<i>"The arrogance of the US was that we felt as though we have already laid such groundwork in the war against Iraq. We / Clinton admin. must have thought everyone in the Arab world loved us….guess we were wrong."</i><br>
<br>
US arrogance is deep. What gives the US such tremendous insights into the problems of other countries? It is because of this arrogance that many countries in the world hate us. I don't think for a second that Clinton thought the Arab world was in love with the US or that we were even "allies". Prince Saud has been working with the US since the Gulf War to remove US troops from his country. Saudi's see the continued US occupation in the region as a violation of their trust and goodwill. The US is rather two faced. We would never allow a long term military occupation of our country by foreign forces, but the US thinks it is just peachy that we occupy countries with our military! OK, so the seeds of hatered for the US have been planted by US arrogance.<br>
